  "title": "Bar Manager",
  "description": "<h3>Job Vacancy: Bar Manager</h3><h3>Industry: Food & Beverage / Hospitality</h3><h3>Work Location: Raffles Place / Bayfront, Singapore</h3><p>⸻</p><h3>Salary</h3><p>SGD 4,000</p><p>⸻</p><h3>Working Hours</h3><p>Working Schedule: Shift Basis (To Be Confirmed)</p><p>⸻</p><h3>Monthly Rest Days</h3><p>6 days</p><p>⸻</p><h3>About the Company</h3><p><u>The employer operates a </u><u><strong>coffee shop and bar</strong></u><u>, offering beverage and bar services in a hospitality setting focused on customer experience and service quality.</u></p><p>⸻</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Open and close the bar according to operational requirements</p></li><li><p>Manage daily bar operations, including order taking and beverage preparation</p></li><li><p>Prepare cocktails, specialty drinks, and a variety of beverages, including coffee</p></li><li><p>Assist with ingredient preparation and inventory management</p></li><li><p>Support team members to ensure smooth and efficient service</p></li><li><p>Maintain cleanliness and organization of the bar area</p></li><li><p>Assist with daily operational tasks and other duties as assigned</p></li></ul><p>⸻</p><h3>Job Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Minimum <strong>3 years of relevant experience</strong> in the food and beverage or hospitality industry preferred</p></li><li><p>Customer-focused mindset with a positive and proactive work attitude</p></li><li><p>Strong communication and teamwork skills</p></li><li><p>Self-motivated and able to work efficiently in a fast-paced environment</p></li></ul><p>⸻</p><h3>Benefits</h3><p>Employment terms and benefits in accordance with Ministry of Manpower (MOM) regulations</p><p>⸻</p><h3>Contract</h3><p>Not specified</p><p>⸻</p><h3>Interview Method</h3><p>Video interview or On-site interview</p>",
